---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Shopify Development Agency"
  description="Codivex delivers high-converting Shopify development services including custom themes, app integrations, checkout extensibility, and performance optimization for DTC and enterprise retail."
  keywords="shopify development agency, shopify developer, custom shopify theme, checkout extensibility, shopify app development"
>
  <section class="relative pt-36 pb-20 overflow-hidden bg-surface">
    <!-- Backlights -->
    <div class="absolute top-1/4 left-1/4 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-primary-maroon/10 rounded-full blur-[120px] pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(to_right,rgba(193,199,207,0.02)_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(to_bottom,rgba(193,199,207,0.02)_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:4rem_4rem] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 relative z-10">
      
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold text-primary-accent hover:text-white transition-colors uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-8 focus:outline-none">
        ← Back to Overview
      </a>

      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="max-w-[800px] mb-16">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-green-500/20 bg-green-500/5 text-[10px] font-bold text-green-400 tracking-[0.1em] uppercase mb-4">
          Commerce Standard
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          Enterprise Shopify Development. <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-secondary-silver via-white to-primary-accent bg-clip-text text-transparent">Engineered for Scale.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-secondary-silver leading-relaxed">
          From pixel-perfect custom Liquid themes to headless Hydrogen storefronts, we build high-converting shopping experiences that integrate seamlessly with your operational flow.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Specs & Performance Highlights -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-20">
        <div class="p-6 border border-outline-ghost bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant/70 font-semibold block mb-2">Primary Metric</span>
          <span class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white block mb-1">+35% Avg. Lift</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-secondary-silver">Conversion rate optimization after audit implementation.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 border border-outline-ghost bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant/70 font-semibold block mb-2">Performance Focus</span>
          <span class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white block mb-1">&lt;1.8s LCP</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-secondary-silver">Server response and asset load tuning across collection nodes.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 border border-outline-ghost bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant/70 font-semibold block mb-2">Architecture</span>
          <span class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white block mb-1">Native v2 Extensibility</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-secondary-silver">Zero reliance on outdated, blocking script tags.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Service Categories Details -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-20" id="optimization">
        
        <!-- Left Side: Features -->
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">Our Shopify Capabilities</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-default bg-primary-maroon/20 border border-primary-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-accent shrink-0 font-bold text-sm">01</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white mb-2">Custom Liquid Themes</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed">
                  Tailored storefront code matching exact Figma prototypes. Built lightweight and modular using Shopify OS 2.0 sections to grant your content team complete layouts control without code.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-default bg-primary-maroon/20 border border-primary-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-accent shrink-0 font-bold text-sm">02</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white mb-2">Checkout Extensibility Migration</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed">
                  Upgrading legacy `checkout.liquid` layouts to native Checkout Extensibility. Secure, stable checkout extensions utilizing custom branding, delivery functions, and upsell chips.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-default bg-primary-maroon/20 border border-primary-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-accent shrink-0 font-bold text-sm">03</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-white mb-2">Custom App & API Integrations</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed">
                  Connecting inventory streams, syncing external CRM systems (Salesforce, HubSpot), and writing secure API scripts to keep storefront operations unified.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Side: Tech Spec Details Card -->
        <div class="p-8 border border-outline-ghost/40 bg-surface-container rounded-lg relative overflow-hidden" id="audits">
          <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-24 h-24 bg-primary-maroon/10 rounded-full blur-2xl pointer-events-none"></div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs border-b border-outline-ghost/20 pb-4">Technology Node Specifications</h3>
          
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Storefront Engines</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">Liquid, Hydrogen Toolkit</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Scripting API</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">Shopify Functions (Rust / WASM)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Checkout Tech</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">Shopify Pixels, Custom Extensions</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-ghost/20">
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Inventory Sync</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">GraphQL Admin API, Webhooks</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 font-semibold text-secondary-silver">Security Level</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-right text-white">SOC2 Compliant, Level 1 PCI DSS</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          
          <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-surface-container-low border border-outline-ghost/50 rounded-default text-xs text-on-surface-variant">
            <strong class="text-white block mb-1">Theme & App Audit Program:</strong> We inspect existing Shopify systems to root out slow third-party Javascript apps, replacing them with native themes elements or Shopify Metaobjects.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Action Footer -->
      <div class="p-8 border border-primary-accent/20 bg-primary-maroon/5 rounded-lg flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-1">Ready to engineer a high-performance storefront?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-secondary-silver">Book a tech strategy call to map your migration and features scope.</p>
        </div>
        <a 
          href="/#contact" 
          class="w-full sm:w-auto px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-primary-maroon border border-primary-accent/40 rounded-default glow-btn-primary hover:text-white transition-all shadow-lg text-center"
        >
          Book Strategy Call
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 md:py-28 bg-surface border-t border-outline-ghost/30">
    <div class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 max-w-[760px] mx-auto">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-primary-accent/20 bg-primary-maroon/10 text-[10px] font-bold text-primary-accent tracking-[0.16em] uppercase mb-5">
          Shopify FAQs
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-5">
          Common Questions About Shopify Development
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-secondary-silver leading-relaxed">
          These answers cover the most common search intents around Shopify theme development, migration, checkout upgrades, and performance optimization.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4">
        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7" open>
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">What does a Shopify developer do for an ecommerce store?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            A Shopify developer builds and improves the storefront, custom themes, apps, integrations, checkout experience, and performance layer so the store is easier to use, faster to load, and better aligned with sales goals.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Can you migrate my store to Shopify or upgrade an existing Shopify theme?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Yes. We support migrations from other platforms and Shopify theme upgrades that modernize layout systems, improve maintainability, and preserve SEO structure while reducing friction for shoppers.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">What is Shopify checkout extensibility and why does it matter?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Checkout extensibility allows merchants to add branded, flexible checkout enhancements using supported Shopify capabilities instead of older methods that limit scalability and create long-term maintenance issues.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Do you build custom Shopify apps and integrations?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Yes. We build custom apps, private integrations, and API workflows for inventory syncing, CRM connectivity, fulfillment logic, and other operational processes that need to fit your business model precisely.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-outline-ghost/50 bg-surface-container-low p-6 md:p-7">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">How can Shopify development improve conversion rates and site speed?</span>
            <span class="text-2xl text-primary-accent transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant/90">
            Better Shopify development improves loading performance, removes unnecessary app overhead, streamlines navigation and product discovery, and creates a cleaner checkout flow that reduces abandonment and supports stronger conversion outcomes.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does a Shopify developer do for an ecommerce store?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A Shopify developer builds and improves the storefront, custom themes, apps, integrations, checkout experience, and performance layer so the store is easier to use, faster to load, and better aligned with sales goals."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you migrate my store to Shopify or upgrade an existing Shopify theme?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. We support migrations from other platforms and Shopify theme upgrades that modernize layout systems, improve maintainability, and preserve SEO structure while reducing friction for shoppers."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is Shopify checkout extensibility and why does it matter?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Checkout extensibility allows merchants to add branded, flexible checkout enhancements using supported Shopify capabilities instead of older methods that limit scalability and create long-term maintenance issues."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you build custom Shopify apps and integrations?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. We build custom apps, private integrations, and API workflows for inventory syncing, CRM connectivity, fulfillment logic, and other operational processes that need to fit your business model precisely."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How can Shopify development improve conversion rates and site speed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Better Shopify development improves loading performance, removes unnecessary app overhead, streamlines navigation and product discovery, and creates a cleaner checkout flow that reduces abandonment and supports stronger conversion outcomes."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
</script>
